<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Marrs on 06-14-2001 07:26 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Just to chuck in my 2cp. When I am fighting in groups, I always have CHeal, Celest Heal and Remedy memmed. CHeal for Wars, Pallys, SKs and usually Rangers. Celest for Bards, and sometimes Rangers depending on the buffs. Remedy on Casters and sometimes Bards, again dependsing on the buffs. I just find when it comes to CHeal that its still really hard to time on anyone with low HP. It just takes ages to get the spell off so has to be timed with great precision, where it is a great deal easier on Wars, Pallys, SKs and Rangers. I can however agree that if my casters have more then 3K worth of HP then it would be much more mana efficient to use CHeal instead, but I have never been in that situation. As I said timing is everything with healing of any type and you just have to get used to it, and yes PLed clerics have a disadvantage where that is concerned as they have not had the opportunity to get group exp. This is just MHO so take as you wish. But I have never failed using this method of healing.

------------------
Marrs Pureheart 
52 Vicar
The Tribunal Server

"May the power of Tunare guide you in your journeys"</TEXTAREA>
